- **Target word count:** 1,100-1,300 words.
- **Tone:** Knowledgeable friend giving practical advice. Not academic, not promotional, not listicle-style.
- **Sentence structure:** Short declarative sentences. Two short sentences over one compound sentence.
- **Paragraph length:** 2-4 sentences maximum. Dense paragraphs lose mobile readers and reduce dwell time.
- **No filler introductions.** The first sentence of the article must contain the primary keyword and begin answering the query.
- **Every H2 section opens with its answer,** not with context or background.
- **Date-stamp all figures.** Every dollar amount, square footage benchmark, percentage, and market statistic must include "(as of Q1 2025)" adjacent to the claim.
- **Tables:** Use clean Markdown or HTML. No merged cells. No decorative formatting. Two tables required: subtype comparison and rent-by-market. See Section 7c for exact column headers and row content.
- **Definitions:** Five key terms must be defined in single clear sentences at first use. See Section 7c, Rule 3 for exact definitions.
- **Proof points:** Five specific numerical claims must appear in the article. See Section 7c, Rule 4 for exact formatting.
- **FAQ section:** Seven Q&A entries, 40-60 words each, at the end of the article. See Section 7c, Rule 5 for exact questions.
- **Schema to implement:** Article schema + FAQPage schema (required on all /knowledgebase/ content). Add Speakable schema to the opening definition paragraph and the FAQ section. HowTo schema is not warranted for this content type.
- **CTAs:** Three placements. Use exact language specified in Section 8. Do not alter CTA wording. Do not add